verbose_text: In addition, the decrease in the frequency of Nrp-1 - Rorgt - Foxp3 + T cells in the PPs in GF-AF mice (Supplemental XREF_FIG) may also be involved in the induction of the antigen specific IgA response, because Foxp3 + T cells induce GC and IgA responses by generating GC Tfh cells and their depletion causes the loss of specific IgA responses.
evidence: Foxp3 +  T cells induce GC and IgA responses by generating GC
